.TH "vmw_bo_init" 9 "vmw_bo_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_bo_init \- Initialize a vmw buffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_bo_init
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *vmw_bo "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "struct ttm_placement *placement "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ","
.BI "bool pin "  ","
.BI "void (*bo_free)(struct ttm_buffer_object *bo) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Pointer to the device private struct
.IP "vmw_bo" 12
Pointer to the struct vmw_buffer_object to initialize.
.IP "size" 12
Buffer object size in bytes.
.IP "placement" 12
Initial placement.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Whether waits should be performed interruptible.
.IP "pin" 12
If the BO should be created pinned at a fixed location.
.IP "bo_free" 12
The buffer object destructor.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative error code on error.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that on error, the code will free the buffer object.
